# GitHub Pages Deployment Guide

Follow these simple steps to put your website online for free.

## Step 1: Create a GitHub Account
1. Go to [github.com](https://github.com/signup).
2. Sign up with your email and verify your account.

## Step 2: Create a New Repository
1. Log in to GitHub.
2. Click the **+** icon in the top-right corner and select **New repository**.
3. In the "Repository name" box, type exactly:
   **snekanthbabu.github.io**
   *(Note: Using this exact format `username.github.io` is important for the main site).*
4. Make sure **Public** is selected.
5. Click **Create repository**.

## Step 3: Upload Your Files
1. On your new repository page, click the link that says **uploading an existing file**.
2. Locate the `portfolio` folder on your computer (where we saved all the code).
3. Select ALL files and folders inside `portfolio` ([index.html](file:///C:/Users/sneka/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7ec1a09f-1266-4104-92a9-6f2be92d706f/portfolio/index.html), [css](file:///C:/Users/sneka/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7ec1a09f-1266-4104-92a9-6f2be92d706f/portfolio/css/style.css), [js](file:///C:/Users/sneka/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7ec1a09f-1266-4104-92a9-6f2be92d706f/portfolio/js/main.js), `games`, `assets`, etc.).
   *Tip: You can drag and drop the entire content of the portfolio folder.*
4. Wait for them to upload.
5. In the "Commit changes" box at the bottom, type "Initial website upload".
6. Click **Commit changes**.

## Step 4: Verify Deployment
1. Wait about 3-5 minutes.
2. Open your browser and go to:
   `https://snekanthbabu.github.io`
3. Your website should be live!

## How to Update Content Later
1. **Edit on Computer**: Open the [.html](file:///C:/Users/sneka/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7ec1a09f-1266-4104-92a9-6f2be92d706f/portfolio/games.html) file (e.g., [experience.html](file:///C:/Users/sneka/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7ec1a09f-1266-4104-92a9-6f2be92d706f/portfolio/experience.html)) in a text editor (like Notepad or VS Code).
2. **Make Changes**: Change text, add new jobs, or fix typos.
3. **Upload Again**: Go to your GitHub repository > Add file > Upload files > Upload the changed file > Commit changes.
4. The site will update automatically in a few minutes.

## How to Add Real Links (LinkedIn / GitHub)
1. Open [contact.html](file:///C:/Users/sneka/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7ec1a09f-1266-4104-92a9-6f2be92d706f/portfolio/contact.html).
2. Find the line that looks like:
   `<a href="#" class="btn-outline">GitHub</a>`
3. Replace `#` with your actual link:
   `<a href="https://github.com/yourusername" class="btn-outline">GitHub</a>`
4. Save and upload.
